<p>I'm trying to connect to RabbitMQ server using SSL but i'm getting this error "SSL peer cert verification failed".</p>  <p>I check the certificate using openssl like so: openssl s_client -connect host:port -CAfile cacert.pem</p>  <p>And got "Verify return code: 0 (ok)" so i believe that the certificate is OK.</p>  <p>I'm trying to use the amqps_bind.c example in <a href="https://github.com/alanxz/rabbitmq-c/blob/master/examples/amqps_bind.c" rel="nofollow">here</a>.</p>  <p>I only need server verification so I removed the amqp_ssl_socket_set_key().</p>  <p>The code is failing in amqp_socket_open().</p>  <p>Also i have a C# code that can connect to the same server using SSL without any errors.</p>